<br>
Earlier discussions can be found here: <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showMessage?topicID=554.topic">The Gospel of Boots of Bladecalling</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> and <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showMessage?topicID=557.topic">Boots of Bladecalling Again</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.<br>
<br>
Simply put, these boots are awesome, and worth whatever effort it takes to obtain them.<br>
<br>
There are several disputes regarding these boots.<br>
<br>
First, many claim they should be ignored in discussions of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> damage output, as few <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> have them.  While this is a valid concern, and non-bootied <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> should be considered, the boots are important equipment, easier to obtain than <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Primal</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, harder to obtain than <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> haste</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  I think they must be included, as should non-bootied Mages.<br>
<br>
Second, it is claimed that these boots are practically impossible to obtain, because there is a narrow window where a guild would be interested in doing <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Velketor The Enormous Sorceror</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Either your guild is not yet capable of doing it, or has gone beyond him.<br>
<br>
Whereas I promised <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Grumples</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> not to say that anything is a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;social problem&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->...uhm....uhm...I will say that once your guild is capable of doing it, it is a matter of convincing them of the importance of this item to you as a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  I discuss this in the Gospel referenced above.<br>
<br>
Here is a little history of how I got mine that may be of some use to you.  Our guild is an up and coming second tier guild, somewhere between the third and sixth most powerful guild on our young server, depending on how you measure.  For example, a couple days ago we did <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Vindicator</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> for the third time.<br>
<br>
We are and were <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>well</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> beyond <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Velketor</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Aamilae</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, at that time my senior and an epicked, bootied <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> ArchMage</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, went to bat with the leadership of my guild, and insisted that we slay <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Velketor</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  More than one officer was dubious, and thought the raid was not a good use of guild effort.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Aamilea</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> pressed ahead, and lead the raid successfully.  I now have my boots.<br>
<br>
Since then, I have made it clear exactly how valuable they are to me, <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>and the guild</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->, especially on long fights.  It allows me, if necessary, to dump my entire mana bar in rods, and nuke continuously without getting aggro.<br>
<br>
The attitude of the guild leadership has changed.  It is now a specific goal of the guild that every post-55 <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> eventually get <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Boots of Bladecalling</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
The bottom line: you give a lot to your guild, a lot of play time that is frankly less than exciting.  You summon rods, focus items, and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Call of the Hero</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> like a good soldier, and you deserve your loot too.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Velketor</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is very straightforward encounter, and if your guild has moved beyond him, well, it won't take that much time to kill him, will it?<br>
<br>
You deserve it.<br>
<br>
If your guild is not yet capable of doing <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Velketor</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, then make it a goal to strive towards.  It is a classic fight, and represents a milestone for your guild.<br>
<br>
