<br>
It's hardly a choice.  It's frankly selfish to ask your guild to do an entire raid strictly for you, which is why I will never ask.  Sure, Velks drops other things, but his other drops for other classes aren't good enough to warrent doing it rather than some other, far more valuable raid.  Why should the guild stop doing something useful for the 12+ melees and instead go help their 1 mage?  I'm a big fan of efficiency and number crunching, and doing Velakator simply doesn't make sense.  That he happens to drop a valuable magician item is mostly just a shame, that he doesn't drop equally useful things for other people, too.<br>
<br>
Compare to a Kael/TOV type raid, where literally everyone can benefit.<br>
<br>
And I'm not sure how you can say they are easier to get than primals but harder than haste.  Um?  There is a haste item that drops in Runnyeye, another one that drops in LGuk and another that drops in Howling Stones.  These are all easily camped for and obtained.  Any level 50 melee who doesn't own at least a FBSS doesn't own one purely out of lack of trying.  I gave a FBSS to my cleric twink, for heavens sake, they sell for less than a Shrunken Goblin Skull Earring.  On my VZ guild, I didn't know of any melee still using a FBSS by level 51, and VZ was way behind the times in loot farming.<br>
<br>
And primals are &quot;easier&quot; in that your guild will be hunting for them a lot more than they'll be killing Velkator.<br>
<br>
Now if the boots dropped off of Ragefire, then I think you'd have a strong argument for factoring boots into mage balance: Ragefire has a lifespan of about 30 seconds, doing him is an event guilds tend to try to arrange as often as possible.<br>
<br>
Incidentally, this is also part of the problem with the mage epic: the only reason to go up so far into Sky these days is for the mage epic.  The warrior epic is, frankly, crap.  With that out of the picture, the main reason guilds do Sky is out of a sense of fairness.  Perhaps you can use that as leverage to talk them into going to Velks, but I find the whole thing to be rather tasteless.  &quot;Let's go to Velks and do a raid that results in me, personally, getting phat lewt.  Some of you may die!  But I'm willing to take that risk.&quot;<br>
<br>
Meh.  Maybe I'm just not enough of a loot whore, but I don't believe in doing raids that only benefits one class, especially a class that represents such a minority in the guild.<br>
<br>
<br>
That said, they are a huge boost to the mage who gets them, I just think they exist in a too far out-of-the-way place to factor them into mage balance.<br>
